      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-12-31T03:21:58Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "it is a bit concerning that this not very high perf code\nhttps://source.chromium.org/chromium/_/chromium/infra/luci/luci-go/+/3e7a396da3f43b9a89eafdf8543498d6ec83b4b6:common/tsmon/store/inmemory.go;l\u003d204;drc\u003de803803befeeeac823fe0a5efeb44de3d37b097a\n\nwill run on each request, in a blocking manner, 4 times\n\ncan we just offload this to a background goroutine?",
      "revId": "d51a19b7f65d07f71250ce889c180389fb9d25c9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ceba7666_2fb5d760",
        "filename": "server/limiter/limiter.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 154,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-01-02T21:55:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Fine, but it complicates the API. The correct solution is to fix tsmon to suck less. There\u0027s already many metrics updated per each request (6 to be precise).\n\nI set frequency of updates pretty high since I want this metric to be observable with lowish latency via /admin/portal/tsmon/metrics (I think it would be useful when debugging production issues).",
      "parentUuid": "c567e5c0_b72d225e",
      "revId": "d51a19b7f65d07f71250ce889c180389fb9d25c9",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
